The Cauterist Synod has resumed unauthorized re-firing ceremonies in the kiln district, using the administrative confusion from the burn ledger recovery as cover for their operations. Cauterist acolytes are maintaining the ritual infrastructure, brand cantors are conducting the sacramental authorization sequences, and re-firing deacons are overseeing the actual re-firing process. Eliminate one of each to break the current ceremonial cycle before it validates new Synod territorial claims.
The Cauterist re-firing ceremony has been disrupted. Acolyte, cantor, and deacon operations have been shut down, and the current ceremonial cycle cannot proceed without completing the sacramental sequence. The ration adjudicator's office has recorded the disruption as a compliance victory and forwarded evidence of unauthorized re-firing to the Southern Oasis Casualty Ledger for inclusion in the pending jurisdictional violation report.

